U||   Grace MacGowan Cooke (1863– ) is a writer all of whose work has
U||   interest and perdurable stuff in it, but few are the authors whose
U||   achievements in the American short story stand out as a whole. In A
U||   Call (August, 1906, Harper’s) she surpasses herself and is not perhaps
