U||   faces of the listening crowd, and the Colonel slightly winced. But he
U||   recovered himself instantly, and continued:
U||   “My client, the only daughter of a widowed mother—who has for years
U||   stemmed the varying tides of adversity—in the western precincts of this
U||   town—stands before you to-day invested only in her own innocence. She
U||   wears no—er—rich gifts of her faithless admirer—is panoplied in no
U||   jewels, rings, nor mementoes of affection such as lovers delight to
U||   hang upon the shrine of their affections; hers is not the glory with
