U||   not unimportant feature of religious exercise known as ‘taking a
U||   collection.’ The defendant, on this occasion, by the mute presentation
U||   of a tip plate covered with baize, solicited the pecuniary
U||   contributions of the faithful. On approaching the plaintiff, however,
U||   he himself slipped a love-token upon the plate and pushed it towards
