U||   however, to publicly abandon his rights here, I can only ask your
U||   Honor’s permission to suspend further proceedings until I can confer
U||   with Colonel Starbottle.”
U||   “As far as I can follow the pleadings,” said the Judge, gravely, “the
U||   case seems to be hardly one for litigation, and I approve of the
U||   defendant’s course, while I strongly urge the plaintiff to accept it.”
U||   Colonel Starbottle bent over his fair client. Presently he rose,
U||   unchanged in look or demeanor. “I yield, your Honor, to the wishes of
U||   my client, and—er—lady. We accept.”
U||   Before the court adjourned that day it was known throughout the town
