U||   descends to Mars’ Pendleton. Three hundred dollars. Uncle Mose is
U||   plenty able to pay now. When dat railroad buy my lan’ I laid off to pay
U||   fur dem mules. Count de money, Mars’ Pendleton. Dat’s what I sold dem
U||   mules fur. Yessir.”
U||   Tears were in Major Talbot’s eyes. He took Uncle Mose’s hand and laid
U||   his other upon his shoulder.
U||   “Dear, faithful, old servitor,” he said in an unsteady voice, “I don’t
U||   mind saying to you that ‘‘Mars’ Pendleton spent his last dollar in the
