U||   “Your crowd rather got the better of us there,” he admitted with the
U||   keen appreciation of one still quite close to college days.
U||   “Of course, the mater is furious, but I rather look on it as a lark.”
U||   She thawed like an April icicle.
U||   “It’s perfectly jolly,” she laughed with him. “Awfully selfish of us,
U||   too, I know, but such loads of fun.”
U||   They were close to the Tutt House now, and her limp, that had entirely
